message.content: Let the smallest of the five consecutive even numbers be $x.$ Then the other four consecutive even numbers are $x+2,$ $x+4,$ $x+6,$ and $x+8.$ Their sum is $320,$ so $$x + (x+2) + (x+4) + (x+6) + (x+8) = 320.$$Simplifying the left side gives $5x + 20 = 320,$ so $5x = 300$ and $x = \boxed{60}.$
